.SH "OVERVIEW"
.IX Header "OVERVIEW"
This section will find and include a located hunk of Pod.  In general, it will
find a \f(CW\*(C`=head1\*(C'\fR command with a content of the plugin's name.
.PP
In other words, if your configuration include:
.PP
.Vb 2
\&  [Generic]
\&  header = OVERVIEW
.Ve
.PP
\&...then this weaver will look for \*(L"=head1 \s-1OVERVIEW\*(R"\s0 and include it at the
appropriate location in your output.
.PP
Since you'll probably want to use Generic several times, and that will require
giving each use a unique name, you can omit \f(CW\*(C`header\*(C'\fR if you provide a
plugin name, and it will default to the plugin name.  In other words, the
configuration above could be specified just as:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&  [Generic / OVERVIEW]
.Ve
.PP
If the \f(CW\*(C`required\*(C'\fR attribute is given, and true, then an exception will be
raised if this section can't be found.
